## 4. Animations (Framer Motion)

Use the **centralized animation system** in `@/lib/animations.ts`:

```tsx
import { motionProps, transitions } from "@/lib/animations";
import { motion } from "framer-motion";

<motion.div {...motionProps.fadeInUp}>
  <h2>Content</h2>
</motion.div>;
```

### Available Presets

| Preset                    | Effect             |
| :------------------------ | :----------------- |
| `motionProps.fadeInUp`    | Fade in from below |
| `motionProps.fadeInLeft`  | Fade in from left  |
| `motionProps.fadeInRight` | Fade in from right |
| `motionProps.fadeIn`      | Simple fade in     |

### Available Variants

`fadeInUp`, `fadeInDown`, `fadeInLeft`, `fadeInRight`, `fadeIn`, `scaleIn`

### Transitions

`transitions.default` (0.6s), `transitions.fast` (0.3s), `transitions.slow` (0.8s), `transitions.spring`

### Rules

- Always use `viewport: { once: true }` — animations should only play once
- Use `transitions.staggered(index)` for list animations
- Never animate layout-shifting properties without `layout` prop

