## 5. Content & CMS (Contentful)

- Blog content managed in **Contentful CMS**
- Fetched via `@/services/blogService.ts` using `@/lib/contentful.ts` client
- Rich text rendered with `@contentful/rich-text-react-renderer`
- Preview client available for draft content when `CONTENTFUL_PREVIEW_TOKEN` is set
- Revalidation: sitemap revalidates hourly (`revalidate = 3600`)
- On-demand revalidation available via `/api/revalidate` route

---

## 6. Naming & Clean Code

- **Path Alias**: `@/*` resolves to `src/*`
- **Component directories**: `PascalCase/` containing `PascalCase.tsx`
- **Variables/Functions**: `camelCase`
- **Constants**: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- **Import Order**:
  1. External libraries (React, Next.js, Framer Motion)
  2. Components (atoms → molecules → organisms → templates)
  3. Lib (utils, animations, contentful)
  4. Services
  5. Data/Types
- **Decomposition**: If a template exceeds 400 lines, break into smaller sections

---

## 7. Performance

- Prefer **Server Components** for SEO content (blog pages, static sections)
- Use `next/image` `<Image>` for all images (automatic optimization)
- Lazy load below-the-fold sections with `dynamic()` if heavy
- Keep Third-party scripts loading with `strategy="afterInteractive"` (GTM, analytics)
- Minimize client-side JS — every KB matters for Core Web Vitals

---

## 8. Anti-Patterns

- ❌ Using `<img>` instead of Next.js `<Image>`
- ❌ Hardcoded hex colors or pixel values
- ❌ Missing `metadata` export on page components
- ❌ Creating new animation variants inline instead of using `@/lib/animations`
- ❌ Skipping heading hierarchy (`<h1>` → `<h3>` without `<h2>`)
- ❌ Adding heavy client-side libraries to Server Components
- ❌ Forgetting to update `sitemap.ts` when adding new pages
- ❌ Using `console.log` in production code
